Lending Tree¶

Data Analysis Lifecycle, Kernel Density Estimation (KDE), Principal Component Analysis (PCA)

Notebook setup here ...

Situation¶

LendingTree is an online lending exchange that connects consumers with multiple lenders, banks, and credit partners who compete for business. Since being founded in 1998 LendingTree has facilitated more than 32 million loan requests.

  • Role: Banker.
  • Business Decision: Lend to whom?
  • Approach: Use kernel density estimation and principal component analysis to look for features that distinguish known good vs. bad loans, and use that insight to inform decisions about new loan applications.
  • Dataset: Lending Tree Loans 2007-2010 ()

Hyper-Parameters¶

This model's parameters were determined by 1 hyper-parameter:

  1. Fraction of observations to hide
fraction of observations to hide
0.05

Parameters¶

This model is defined by 4 parameters:

  1. Polygon vertices for high certainty good loans
  2. Polygon vertices for high certainty bad loans
  3. Polygon vertices for moderate certainty good loans
  4. Polygon vertices for moderate certainty bad loans
If new observation is within this space, then predict it's a good loan with high certainty:
